title: Bold, Quirky, Unique, Limited Edition, Fashion Brand Logo Design
description:
I sell handmade, limited edition, unique, bow ties, pocket squares and cufflinks. My website is http://www.blueeyesbowties.com I want a logo that has an emblem as well as the written name.
PLEASE NOTE: I will be getting a new website after my logo is designed so don't feel like you need to use my current colour scheme as this will change depending on my new logo. I designed my current logo on Canva so it's super basic and quite childish. I really want to move away from this as my brand is now growing.
TO NOTE...
It is extremely important that the emblem part of the logo can stand alone and be recognisable without the writing. I want to be able to use the emblem separately to the words. I really like how the designs I’ve included as examples have a distinct emblem and the brand is easily identifiable without the written name.
I want my new logo to represent not only what I sell but also the values of Blue Eyes Bow Ties.
CORE VALUES:
• Providing quality, entirely handmade accessories
• Always providing a personal service – I chat with many of my customers via email and build a relationship with them. Many come back to shop time and again.
• Producing accessories that are truly unique and always limited edition
• Having a wide selection of daring, bold and quirky bow ties alongside classic and simple designs
I make everything on my website myself by hand, and all of my items are limited in number to just a few; each item is truly unique.
I am PASSIONATE about beautiful fabrics and most of my designs are bold and quirky. I’d like this to be captured in my new logo.
TARGET AUDIENCE
I have a somewhat varied target audience which is mainly men, but I definitely sell to women too. The emblem should lean towards the masculine. Age ranges from 20s-80s but my target audience is roughly in the middle of this range. My ideal customer is someone who doesn’t mind paying a bit extra for a special and unique accessory.
Bow ties are priced from £30-£150. I charge relatively high process for my products and therefore do not want my logo to look cheap or gimmicky. I also plan to make higher value items in the future, as the higher end bow ties have been really popular, and I want to grow that side of my business.
Blue Eyes Bow Ties is a long name, so I need you to find a creative way to show it to its best advantage.
DESIGN IDEAS
I love the pop of colour in the Paul Smith zebra Logo and I love the logo in general because it's fun but also clearly high-end. My bow ties are bold and colourful so this could be a feature of my logo. I also like the Paul Smith font which is both creative and personal. I like the quirkiness of the Vivienne Westwood logo. However, I do not want copies of these logos, they are just to show you what I value in a logo design.
Please do not send me logos that contain basic drawings of eyes or things like a bearded man in a bow tie! I need something unique, and which captures the core values of my business.
Feel free to get in touch if you’d like more detail.
I’m really excited to see your designs. Thanks so much!
other_notes: Please read my full brief in the description above, as I give full details of what I'm looking for. Thank you!

title: BAMF | Design or illustrate/draw a badass new logo for an iconic brand's new website "BAMF.COM"
description:
BAMF is a leading growth marketing agency, content publisher, tech developer, and community of "Badass Marketers & Founders" around the world.
We are also releasing a badass new NFT collection in a month, and a new BAMF apparel clothing line this year. New books, a possible comic book series + games based on our NFTs.
The brand, like our name, is EXPLODING and taking over!
This new logo needs to be versatile to work everywhere and be recognizable and readable in an instant.
We are based in Venice Beach, California, and have punk rock, surfer/skateboarder, vibe, and generally "rebel" vibe.
Brands I like for reference: VICE, VANS, VOLCOM, NIKE, SUPREME.
They all have strong black and white iconic style logos with a bit of a "street/rebel/skate" style, which is what I want.
Please review this Pinterest "BAMF Branding" mood/inspiration board that I made to give you a direction of the aesthetic and style that I like and want to convey with our new BAMF logo: [https://www.pinterest.com/houstongolden/bamf-branding](https://www.pinterest.com/houstongolden/bamf-branding)
We've recently acquired [BAMF.COM](http://bamf.com/) !!! And we are launching new products and service lines as mentioned above, so we are evolving our branding to match our new level as a company.
I'm open to pure typography-based logos, and logos that are typography + an accent/icon graphic if it's minimal tasteful and represents BAMF. Love most surf/skateboard brand logos styles.
I am not tied to any style.
Challenge is being BOLD. Strong. Edgy. Badass.... while also being "high-end, modern, polished."
We are both a high-end agency offering influencer/content marketing services for B2B brands and celebrity entrepreneurs like Jay Shetty, Prince Ea, Russell Brunson, and many more.... thus, we can't look "too cartoony" unless it looks really cool and crisp.
We are also based our home is in edgy badass Venice beach - where skateboarding was invented, The Doors, Red Hot Chili Peppers, and other rock bands hail from - and we have this rebel lifestyle.
We are high-end rebels.
We are tech, marketing, content, influencer, NFT art, and street/skate/surf apparel.
We are a lot of things. We are badass. We are BAMF.
I'm excited to see how you can take our rapidly growing brand to the next level with a badass logo that truly represents our attitude and all that we are.
Please take the time to scroll through the Pinterest mood board that I created for this project. This will give you a true sense of my style and aesthetic. It's all over the place (I know), but it's there to set the mood and serve as a creative springboard.
Here is the "BAMF Branding Mood Board 2022" on Pinterest: [https://www.pinterest.com/houstongolden/bamf-branding](https://www.pinterest.com/houstongolden/bamf-branding)
I will be managing this project personally and replying to designers and providing feedback as much as I can on my own. This is a project I take very seriously, so I hope you are ready to work with me through creative ideas and revisions.
Let's do this!
Cheers,
Houston Golden
// Founder & CEO at BAMF
other_color_requirements: Black and White only, bold contrast. Please review the Pinterest brand mood/inspo board for reference and direction: https://www.pinterest.com/houstongo…-branding/
other_notes:
Black and White, bold contrast. Please review the Pinterest brand mood and creative inspiration board for reference and direction: https://www.pinterest.com/houstongo…-branding/
I am not tied to any style, but I am picky and will give honest feedback on every design submission based on the criteria I've put here in the brief and the style I've conveyed through the mood board on Pinterest.
Your challenge is balancing being both —
BOLD. Strong. Edgy. Cool. Badass.... while also being HIGH-END, sophisticated, minimal, modern, polished.
Other requirements and requests...
DO THIS:
- Share your logo concept with both a plain solid black and a white background included in a single submission.
- UPPERCASE "BAMF"
- Scroll through this to get a sense of my vibe... "BAMF Branding Mood Board 2022" on Pinterest: https://www.pinterest.com/houstongo…f-branding
DON'T DO THIS:
- Don't post duplicates.
- Please no backward or upside-down letters.
- No “B” icons… that doesn’t add anything and looks redundant in front of BAMF letters…
- Don't include any colors in your logos. Black & White only.
- Letters need to be horizontal, not stacked 2x2 like this. All four UPPERCASE letters across required: BAMF
- Don't render your logo concept on any physical objects - no hats, shirts, posters, bags, biz cards, etc. All logos posted as physical renders like this will be instantly rejected. Again…. no rendering of logos on physical objects, including iPhone. As mentioned in brief.
- Don't post duplicate black/white variations as separate submissions, those should be stacked, side by side, or however you want to include in a single submission how you would like.
- Don't include ".COM" in the logo, just BAMF.
- I'm realizing I'm actually not a big fan of negative space typography style either for our logo at least, even if it shows up in the mood board.
Here are a few other stylistic traits to avoid I'm realizing I don't like in terms of typography direction.
TYPOGRAPHY STYLES TO AVOID...
- too "wavey"
- too "thin" lettering
- too "feminine"
- negative space letters
- backward or upside-down letters
- split or cut in half letters
- lower-case, or capital case... never "bamf" or "Bamf"
TYPOGRAPHY STYLES TO CONSIDER TRYING...
- always UPPERCASE - BAMF, never bamf.
- anything as long as bold/strong and "instantly readable letters"
- Strong, bold, geometric, straight-edged
- Bold italic, or leaning forward, bold with a bit of motion/energy
- a bold cartoony/bubbly style IF it still looks cool and edgy, which I've found is a hard style to achieve, but the VICE logo is the perfect example of this. Somehow still bubble/graffiti typography style, but still looks rock n roll, strong, masculine, edgy.
- A strong graffiti, brush, or any masculine bold font with a creative drop-shadow, outline effect, or custom graphic accent
- Other modern creative font styles
OK... all of this is meant to HELP you avoid wasting time on designs I won't like or just reject....
BUT... I don't want to stifle creativity. I want to see as much creativity as possible. PLEASE SURPRISE ME with your creativity and feel free to offer designs that challenge my requests/requirements if they are truly badass in your mind's eye.
Let's rock 'n roll!
NOTE: if you entered one of our previous logo contests, you are invited to join this new and final contest and re-submit your designs which received a 3+ star rating.

title: Help a City Find its Best Self
description: "What Louisville Could Be . . ." is a project (launched through video interviews) that asks people in Louisville, Kentucky -- a city divided by civil unrest following the killing of Breonna Taylor and seeking a path forward that will bring people together, a city that envies the economic growth of regional peers like Nashville (Tennessee) and Indianapolis (Indiana) and wonders how it can gain jobs and business as they have -- what they want their hometown to be in the future. My wine programs are set up as a tailor-made, all inclusive type approach, i.e. it's always a combination of a vineyard hike, a winery tour and a wine and food pairing, considering the wishes of the customer. For the time being there are no alternatives for such a manifold program along the Mosel wine region and my customers are exactly looking for this comprehensive approach.
Since my wine programs are offered in an higher price range and are addressed to a corresponding audience, I am looking for a solution that offers the diversity of my program, in a modern, stylish way without being kitschy.
The river "Mosel" should be the eye-catcher for the customer, because it is a world famous wine region as well as a fascinating landscape with some of the steepest vineyards in the world. Within this area, I offer supreme wine programs which give the customer a perfect overall impression of landscape, wine and food. This will be expressed with "wine adventures", in German "Wein Erlebnisse".
other_notes: This types of designs match my aesthetic preferences.
